\date{2026-04-15T17:29:05Z}
\title{Cardinality}
\taxon{Definition}

\p{Cardinality can be thought of as the size of a set. For a finite set we can compare cardinalities by simply assigning a number to the amount of elements in the set. We can make a generalized idea to compare the sizes of any sets including infinite ones.}
\transclude{000R}
\p{If there exists a function #{f:A\rightarrow B} that is 1-1 and onto, we say that set #{A} has the same cardinality as set #{B}.}